The paper introduces a new type of feed-forward deep neural network that optimizes computational efficiency by selectively executing only a subset of neurons depending on the input. This topic is closely related to machine learning and neural networks, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the core concepts and techniques of machine learning, including deep neural networks. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper focuses on image classification tasks. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as it covers the broader field of AI, which includes machine learning and neural networks. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as it covers the study of neural networks and their applications. Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but it covers the design and analysis of complex systems, which could include deep neural networks.
